4
5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING THE LEGISLATIVE AUDIT DIVISION TO AUDIT THE
6 MONTANA STATE BAR ASSOCIATION COLLECTION OF THE ANNUAL ATTORNEY LICENSE TAX; AND
7 REQUIRING THE JUDICIAL BRANCH TO COVER THE COST OF THE AUDIT; AND AMENDING SECTION
8 5-13-102, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Audit state bar of Montana of attorney license tax collection. (1)
13 There must be a one-time performance financial audit of the state bar of Montana collection of the attorney
14 license tax provided for in 37-61-211. The performance financial audit must be conducted by or at the direction
15 of the legislative auditor and may include but is not limited to the collection and use of the attorney license tax
16 and the current contract for the collection of the license tax with the state bar of Montana:
17 (a) an audit creating a thorough understanding of each funding source and how the state bar of
18 Montana is funded and from where, how much money is received from each funding source, and how each
19 dollar from each source is spent over the past 10 years; and
20 (b) an analysis of budgets, costs, and functions of the state bar of Montana over time.
21 (2) The legislative auditor shall scope and plan the audit based on risk, including a consideration of
22 the state bar of Montana's financial, operational, and technological risks associated with meeting its intended
23 purpose, goals, objectives, and legal mandates. The legislative auditor shall consider all of the responsibilities,
24 goals, and objectives of the state bar of Montana and the office of disciplinary counsel as part of the legislative
25 auditor's scoping and selection process.
26 (3)(2) The objectives of this audit must be formulated, defined, and conducted in accordance with
27 industry standards established for auditing as described in 5-13-308.
28 (4)(3) The cost of the audit in whole must be paid for by the judicial branch.
